commit_message:
Optimize UnaryStruct memory use for when its unused. Having __init__
create a bytearray buffer costs 32 bytes for every UnaryStruct
even when its not used. This makes code size a bit larger but its
shared amongst all instances.

author: Scott Shawcroft
commit_message:
Introduce StructArray that can be used for repeated register
structures. This is better than a tuple of objects because it
creates fewer objects by default and is a fixed cost per device
independent of the number of entries in the array.

author: Jeff Epler
commit_message:
RWBits: Add support for signed registers

An example of a signed register is the calibration value of the PCF8523
real-time clock, which stores values from -64 to +63 in 7 bits.  This could
now be specified as
    calibration = i2c_bits.RWBits(7, 0xe, 0, signed=True)

Note that assigning a negative value to an RWBits already worked,
regardless of whether the register was signed, so it was already possible
to *write* -2 to the register; this just allows it to be read back as -2
instead of 126.
